# encoquencer: the minimal example — same sequencer core as motoquencer, but on E4
# encoders. One [e4] -> 4 encoders -> a 4-step sequence, all gates on by default,
# all steps at C (0 V, C-lydian). A period-2 clock on I1 advances one step per edge;
# the gate fires per step and startofsequence (O4) fires on the first step + wraps.
# This proves the shared transport/quantize/gate engine runs under the encoder skin.
tickrate 100
patch <<<
[e4]
[encoquencer]
    clock           = I1
    cv              = O1
    gate            = O2
    startofsequence = O4
>>>
@0 expect O2 0 tol 1e-4
@1 set I1 1
@1 expect O1 0 tol 1e-4
@1 expect O2 1 tol 1e-4
@1 expect O4 1 tol 1e-4
@2 set I1 0
@2 expect O2 0 tol 1e-4
@3 set I1 1
@3 expect O2 1 tol 1e-4
@4 set I1 0
@5 set I1 1
@5 expect O2 1 tol 1e-4
@6 set I1 0
@7 set I1 1
@8 set I1 0
@9 set I1 1
@9 expect O4 1 tol 1e-4
